I originally learned this plant as wild chamomile.

CA native

description:
This liverwort has smallish, slightly ruffled leaf structures (thalli).  Thalli are a glossy yellowish-green and appear to be dotted.  The dots are framed with 5-sided borders. 

Many leaves show the characteristic crescent shaped cups.  A few in the photos still contain gemmae, tiny clones of the plant that are washed into the soil by rain. We have had several days of sometimes heavy rain and this is a relatively unprotected spot which might be why there are so few gemmae visible. 

Found alongside the wall of the old Coco-Cola Bottling Company on Miller Way and Stockton Blvd. This wall is shaded all day.
